# Naming and File Conventions

- Keep feature names in `snake_case` folders under `lib/features/`.
- Use standard file names:
  - `<feature>_view.dart`
  - `<feature>_controller.dart`
  - `<feature>_state.dart` or `<feature>_view_state.dart`
  - `presentation/<feature>_view_phone.dart`
  - `presentation/<feature>_view_tablet.dart`
  - `presentation/<feature>_view_desktop.dart`
- Use class names in `PascalCase` matching file intent (for example `RecipesController`).
- Use provider names in `camelCase` with `Provider` suffix.
- Keep use case naming:
  - `<Action><Entity>Usecase`
  - `<Action><Entity>Request`
  - `<Action><Entity>Response`
- Keep repository/data source naming:
  - `<Feature>Repository`
  - `<Feature>DataSourceRemote`
  - `<Feature>DataSourceLocal`
- Match existing neighboring feature style before introducing any new naming pattern.
